context.caption: Colours of the dried floral rainbow. In store now.
Loving this colour palette of mixed fresh  and dried roses for Mell’s wedding bouquets yesterday.
We have a wide array of gorgeous fresh flowers to create something beautiful for you or your loved ones. It doesn’t have to be Valentine’s Day to spoil someone with flowers....

A pair of dried beauties for the new store  Designer Wardrobe Wellington.
@designer.wardrobe

It’s been a crazy three days with Valentine’s Day orders. Thanks so much to all our customers for supporting our wee business. We were so busy we didn’t get many photos of our work, but I had to get some snaps of this bouquet that one of our fave customers bought for her wife. Looking forward to two days off now. We’re back on board Wednesday!

Many hours go into prepping our Lunaria and bunny tails for sale. We strip the seeds and skins off the Lunaria and divide them into different stem lengths and we strip the stems of the bunny tails and divide them into cute little bunches. We grew the lunaria from seed and have saved all the seeds for the next season. Nature is amazing!
Fresh from the drying rack.
Latest haul from the drying room...
During yesterday’s run...
At it again drying whatever we can to add colour to our collection, and most importantly reduce waste. We love doing what we do with dried flowers!

FREE  CHOCOLATE for Valentine’s Day flower orders of $150 and over. That’s right, we will add a scrumptious bar of Wellington Chocolate Factory’s divine chocolate to every fresh or dried Valentine’s order of $150 and over. Please head to the link in our bio to place your order. Offer available while stocks last. 
https://floriade.co.nz/valentines-day
Custom vase designs. One in neutral and the other with pop of orange and yellow.
Sympathy bouquet in a soft garden style.
Rainbow brights in one of our dried bouquets.
Look at this rainbow bouquet of naturally dried flowers created by Mahalia. Loving the joy in this one!

Lunaria annua grown from seed in my own little flower garden. Once I’ve had time to peel back the layers, I will share photos of their beautiful pearlescent interior. The other trick is to save all the seeds inside and start growing from seed all over again. Nature really is incredible.

Loving the colours in this gigantic wreath (over one metre diameter) for The Beauty Room in Lower Hutt. I had a quick tour and this place is super luxurious and a beautiful place to get pampered. One of my new year goals is to spend less time working and more time taking care of myself so I am going to book in for sure! @thebeautyroom_nz 
Wreath from @thevinestnz
Beautiful blues.
Always a nice surprise to see my work when I’m out and about shopping. This one is @lululemonnz in Lambton Quay.

A trio of vases filled to order. We love adding the personal touch to our designs by filling each individual vase according to the customer’s personal colour, form and textural preferences. Or you can ask us to just go for it with the design!
Floral setup for Casey and Reagan’s wedding at Thistle Inn Thorndon yesterday. Copper arch from @thevintagepartynz
Delicate dried floral hair slide for the Wellington Cup this past weekend. I used tweezers to place each delicate element....It’s like doing floral surgery.

Dried arrangement for home. This one features some dyed pink hydrangeas, natural green hydrangeas, copper amaranthus, brunia and bleached Ming fern. It is in a tall vintage Scheurich jug found in an op shop.

Valentine’s Day is fast approaching and things get pretty busy here at Floriade! Get your orders in now as supply will be limited. Head to our website to order (link in bio). Please note orders for Valentine’s close on Wednesday 10th February.
So many dried helichrysum, AKA strawflowers. Each stem individually wired to help them last the distance in our beautiful dried arrangements.
Dried wedding bouquet for Ruth. This lucky bride gets to keep her bouquet for years as a memento of her special day.
Wild whites and greens.

Flowers for a 40th birthday last night at the beautiful restaurant Atlas. 
The private dining room “Atlas Up” has incredible views over Wellington Harbour  @atlas_wellington

Lots of people ask where and how we dry our flowers. Here are some behind the scenes pics of what we do to bring you the huge range of dried florals in our collection . It’s a messy business...I often get covered in bits and pieces of dried flowers stuck to my hair and clothing so I end up looking look like a scarecrow!

A fresh green wreath for a Swedish couple who want to enjoy some memories of Northern European Christmas. It features orange slices dried for many hours in our oven, cinnamon sticks, pine cones and lots of red satin ribbon.  It smells amazing!
Flowers from a wife to her husband to celebrate 30 years of marriage. Imagine getting a bunch of floral love delivered to you at work? Send some love today.
This avante garde beauty went out to a birthday girl at work yesterday. She was very happy I hear.
Did you know you can request a fresh bouquet that’s designed to dry so you can keep it for years to come? Loving this delicate beauty.

We had our third wreath workshop last night and once again everyone made something beautiful and unique to them. I love teaching these workshops because they’re fun and creative and I always learn something too. One of the best things is that so many people start to believe in their own creativity! 
@thevinestnz
Custom coloured hydrangeas.
Our shop window at night. We love how our wreath (made of a recycled Christmas tree) sparkles at night to bring some bling to Cambridge Terrace.

The Christmas wreath at our house made by @mahalia_t 
Isn’t it incredible? This is what you do when you just love colour!
Wedding arch for C and P’s wedding on Saturday. They chose such a gorgeous place to get married amongst the trees @tarurekaestate
Working on multiple projects at once. This time of year it’s late nights most nights to get the work done on time.

One of our last deliveries for the year. What a year 2020 has been. Thanks to all our customers and followers. We couldn’t be where we are without your support, your encouragement and your feedback. Lots of exciting plans for 2021 but right now we are winding down for some family time and a chance to put our feet up. Happy Christmas and may 2021 be a better year all around the world full of love and blessings.

Unbeknownst to us at the time, we had our final Poppy Friday last week. Our darling girl sadly passed away last night. Poppy graced our shop many a Friday this year, keeping us company and doling out endless love and kisses. We are so grateful to her and to her lovely mum for the wonderful time we got to spend together. We will miss you angel.
Feeling blessed to have such a lovely garden to gather foliage from. Next up is the hydrangeas as they’re really starting to bloom now.
Sneak peek of a set of commissioned dried floral sculptures for Te Papa. More info coming soon....
Today’s roadside forage. Yep they’re weeds but they are still beautiful. There is beauty all around us and I am trying to slow down and take notice...
Custom arrangement today with these gorgeous peonies showing off!
So pleased with our dried peonies! Their colour has been preserved perfectly thanks to our drying machine.
A large and romantic dried arrangement custom made for a birthday gift. Featuring some delicate elements we spray painted.
Bit of fun with some peony petals.

Can’t believe this crazy year is already coming to an end! The last day our shop will be open for this year will be Friday the 19th. We will still be taking online orders on Monday 22nd and Tuesday 23rd for delivery or pickup on those days but the shop will be closed. Get your orders in now so you don’t miss out. Happy Holidays!

We had our first wreath workshop last night and everyone made gorgeous wreaths. Thanks for braving the wind and rain to get there. There are only a couple of spaces left in our fourth workshop so please check out our website if you’re keen. 
Thanks for the cupcakes by @lesleighr  and thanks for the calligraphy placecards bu Sara @theessletter

This collection of dried bouquets is very special to the six family members receiving them because they are made entirely with flowers that were in their beloved father’s casket arrangement.
Scroll to see the original casket arrangement.
In case you were wondering what 400 mini dried spray rose heads looks like...here they are ready to go to their new home.

Check out the Wana Ake space at Te Papa on Level 4. It’s a place to find some peace and solitude and read art books (or bring your own!)...my idea of heaven. These five floral sculptures I created will be on display until April. Also check out the World of Wearable Arts exhibition which will be one of my Summer highlights for sure. @te_papa
